WEBVTT

00:00.030 --> 00:01.905
(Carter) Previously on
"Finding Carter"... .

00:01.930 --> 00:03.483
I was six years old when
my mom was attacked.

00:03.508 --> 00:04.444
It was my dad.

00:04.469 --> 00:05.969
I saw him stab her.

00:05.994 --> 00:08.085
- (Taylor) If you hadn't have been there...
- (Gabe) But I was.

00:08.109 --> 00:10.026
- Taylor!
- (Max) Taylor told me what happened.

00:10.051 --> 00:11.566
You know I'd do anything for Taylor.

00:11.800 --> 00:14.035
You should stay out all night more often.

00:14.060 --> 00:15.010
(Carter) I really like him.

00:15.035 --> 00:16.190
- Does Elizabeth know?
- Are you kidding?

00:16.215 --> 00:17.668
How was the all-night concert?

00:17.693 --> 00:18.769
Really special.

00:18.794 --> 00:20.458
You're looking at me in the eye

00:20.483 --> 00:21.728
and I still don't know if you're

00:21.753 --> 00:23.220
telling me the truth.

00:23.245 --> 00:24.658
♪

00:26.489 --> 00:28.204
- Hey.
- Hey.

00:28.838 --> 00:30.655
We've got this whole two ships thing

00:30.680 --> 00:31.863
happening nowadays.

00:31.888 --> 00:33.520
Wait, who are you?

00:33.545 --> 00:36.760
♪ Know that I belong with you ♪

00:37.457 --> 00:38.875
So how are you?

00:38.900 --> 00:40.068
Good.

00:40.093 --> 00:43.260
I didn't even hear you come in last night.

00:43.285 --> 00:44.985
Oh, yeah, I was late.

00:45.181 --> 00:46.706
- How late?
- I don't know.

00:46.731 --> 00:47.502
Bar life.

00:47.527 --> 00:49.320
- Everyone hangs out after work.
- Oh, really?

00:49.345 --> 00:51.810
What? Like drinking?

00:52.222 --> 00:54.023
No, not necessarily.

00:54.048 --> 00:55.673
People tell stories.

00:55.698 --> 00:56.935
Philosophize about life.

00:56.960 --> 00:59.327
Make sculptures out of straws.

00:59.352 --> 01:01.090
- At the bar.
- Yes.

01:01.115 --> 01:03.210
- Where else would I be?
- I don't know.

01:04.004 --> 01:05.462
Is there something you want to ask me?

01:05.488 --> 01:07.204
Just... what you're doing

01:07.229 --> 01:09.996
and who you're with until
3:00, 4:00 in the morning.

01:10.021 --> 01:11.745
- Well, who do you think I'm with?
- I don't know, Carter.

01:11.770 --> 01:13.350
That's why I'm asking.

01:14.455 --> 01:17.646
I see that you're spending
more time with Ben lately.

01:18.212 --> 01:19.507
Well, he is my brother.

01:19.532 --> 01:20.900
Yeah, I know, and I'm glad

01:20.925 --> 01:22.120
you're getting close to him,

01:22.145 --> 01:24.945
but he is only 16,

01:24.970 --> 01:28.222
so it's not like he's, you know...

01:28.247 --> 01:29.485
visiting you at the bar.

01:29.510 --> 01:31.585
And it's not exactly
like I can go visit him

01:31.610 --> 01:33.354
- at school either.
- Right.

01:33.379 --> 01:34.594
So where do you see him?

01:34.619 --> 01:36.145
I don't know, around.

01:37.638 --> 01:39.534
Are you worried I'm
spending time with Lori?

01:39.559 --> 01:41.255
What? No.

01:41.280 --> 01:43.495
You aren't, are you?

01:43.520 --> 01:45.029
I gotta go to work.

01:45.054 --> 01:46.855
Look, Carter.

01:47.097 --> 01:48.230
Carter!

01:48.255 --> 01:50.082
No, I am not spending time with Lori,

01:50.107 --> 01:52.242
as if I should really
have to make that clear.

01:52.267 --> 01:54.162
I'm not looking to fight with you,

01:54.187 --> 01:55.337
it's just...

01:56.497 --> 01:58.240
I miss my daughter

01:58.265 --> 02:01.286
and I want to know what's
going on in her life.

02:01.311 --> 02:03.024
I can't remember the last time

02:03.049 --> 02:05.079
we had an evening together.

02:07.241 --> 02:09.116
Fine.

02:12.327 --> 02:16.231
I have been...  hanging out at Jared's.

02:16.797 --> 02:18.086
Jared.

02:18.111 --> 02:19.335
Your boss?

02:19.359 --> 02:21.661
Jared, my boyfriend.

02:24.003 --> 02:25.003
Carter.

02:25.028 --> 02:26.433
He's way too old for you.

02:26.458 --> 02:28.624
Oh, come on, it's not
like he's 40 or something.

02:28.649 --> 02:31.026
- How long has this been going on?
- What difference does that make?

02:31.051 --> 02:33.734
It makes a big difference,
because I'm your mother

02:33.759 --> 02:36.305
and I get to offer advice
and set some limits.

02:36.330 --> 02:37.722
This is my life.

02:37.747 --> 02:39.222
I get to decide what's right for me

02:39.247 --> 02:41.251
and you don't get to tell
me who I can and can't date.

02:41.276 --> 02:42.448
I'm just trying to protect you.

02:42.473 --> 02:44.001
I don't need your protection.

02:44.026 --> 02:45.481
Well, if you live in this house,

02:45.506 --> 02:47.616
then you have to follow the rules.

02:47.641 --> 02:50.568
Well, maybe I need to find
somewhere else to live, then.

02:53.504 --> 02:55.892
♪ There you go ♪

02:55.917 --> 02:58.371
♪ There you stay ♪

02:58.396 --> 03:00.280
♪ Keeping low ♪

03:00.305 --> 03:02.788
♪ Never want to play ♪

03:02.813 --> 03:05.214
♪ You've been up and down, down ♪

03:05.239 --> 03:07.780
♪ You've been low, low, low ♪

03:07.805 --> 03:12.028
♪ Pretending to not feel alone ♪

03:13.086 --> 03:16.080
♪ Pretending to not feel alone ♪

03:16.105 --> 03:18.554
- Synced and corrected by martythecrazy -
- www.addic7ed.com -

03:20.057 --> 03:21.891
♪

03:22.207 --> 03:23.365
Hey, beautiful.

03:23.390 --> 03:24.824
Hey.

03:28.603 --> 03:30.349
- You okay?
- No.

03:30.374 --> 03:32.416
I just had a huge fight with my mom.

03:32.441 --> 03:33.682
What about?

03:33.707 --> 03:35.152
Lots of things.

03:35.177 --> 03:36.977
I told her I was moving out.

03:37.304 --> 03:38.671
Intense.

03:38.696 --> 03:41.016
Yeah, I know, I'm not
even sure why I said it.

03:41.041 --> 03:43.096
She just pissed me off.

03:43.121 --> 03:44.420
Hey, you'll figure it out.

03:44.445 --> 03:45.778
I don't know if we will.

03:45.803 --> 03:48.724
Ever since Lori's come
back, she's suffocating me.

03:48.749 --> 03:49.749
Hey.

03:51.306 --> 03:53.023
You have a place to crash?

03:54.789 --> 03:56.930
No, I didn't really think that far ahead.

03:56.963 --> 03:58.212
Well, you can always stay with me

03:58.237 --> 04:00.186
for a few nights if you want.

04:00.361 --> 04:03.154
Or if you want to get a place of your own,

04:03.179 --> 04:04.708
I'll front you the dough.

04:05.145 --> 04:07.908
After all, I know where you work.

04:09.426 --> 04:11.524
Thank you.

04:11.549 --> 04:13.043
Boss.

04:14.132 --> 04:15.660
Anything you need.

04:16.829 --> 04:18.195
(Elizabeth) Thanks, let me know.

04:18.220 --> 04:19.197
Hey, question.

04:19.223 --> 04:20.564
Where are we on that tainted drugs

04:20.589 --> 04:21.831
that they found last night?

04:21.856 --> 04:23.463
Tox report just came back.

04:24.207 --> 04:25.602
They're a match for the ones

04:25.627 --> 04:27.194
that killed those kids in Alexandria.

04:27.219 --> 04:29.271
Any update on the kid who took them?

04:29.374 --> 04:30.556
Still in ICU.

04:30.581 --> 04:32.404
The dad's coming in later to talk to you.

04:32.429 --> 04:33.659
Okay, thanks.

04:33.684 --> 04:35.637
Every parent's nightmare.

04:36.477 --> 04:39.011
♪

04:40.303 --> 04:42.318
_

04:46.603 --> 04:50.240
(Taylor) So how about we make a lunch

04:50.414 --> 04:52.528
and have a picnic by the river?

04:52.553 --> 04:54.282
I gotta finish the work I started

04:54.307 --> 04:55.708
on your parents' basement.

04:55.733 --> 04:57.432
I think you can call in sick.

04:57.457 --> 04:58.857
Your mom would kill me.

04:58.882 --> 04:59.832
Fine.

04:59.857 --> 05:01.830
I will text Gabe

05:01.855 --> 05:04.156
and see what him and Damon are doing

05:04.181 --> 05:06.558
and then you can meet up
with us when you're done.

05:07.392 --> 05:10.510
Or I'll just come back and
we can do something mellow.

05:10.535 --> 05:12.518
Like you go and...

05:12.543 --> 05:13.927
Is this about Gabe?

05:13.952 --> 05:15.664
You know, if it makes you feel better,

05:15.689 --> 05:17.208
I don't have to see him as much and...

05:17.234 --> 05:18.460
It's really not.

05:18.485 --> 05:20.104
It's really not about Gabe.

05:20.233 --> 05:22.409
But you're okay?

05:22.982 --> 05:26.089
I'm sorry I didn't tell you earlier.

05:27.233 --> 05:29.520
My dad is up for parole.

05:29.545 --> 05:31.841
Oh my God, Max.

05:33.455 --> 05:35.209
So there's a hearing tomorrow.

05:35.234 --> 05:37.001
I'm...

05:37.331 --> 05:39.105
gonna testify.

05:39.130 --> 05:41.674
Try to get them to keep him in prison.

05:42.357 --> 05:43.479
Okay.

05:43.504 --> 05:44.871
What time do we have to be there?

05:44.896 --> 05:46.674
You don't need to come, I can handle it.

05:46.699 --> 05:48.047
I know you can.

05:48.073 --> 05:49.336
I want to.

05:50.811 --> 05:52.546
Unless you don't want me to.

05:52.571 --> 05:54.376
No, I really appreciate it.

05:54.401 --> 05:56.006
It's just something that

05:56.031 --> 05:58.522
I think I need to do on my own.

06:00.383 --> 06:02.202
Okay.

06:06.831 --> 06:08.655
Table 13 is still waiting on their drinks.

06:08.945 --> 06:10.740
- That's not my table.
- Yeah, it is.

06:10.765 --> 06:12.513
We switched around the sections, remember?

06:12.538 --> 06:14.400
Oh, crap, I totally forgot.

06:14.425 --> 06:16.024
Hang on a sec, let me just get a...

06:18.041 --> 06:21.105
Hey, Carter, it's fine,
I'll take care of them.

06:21.769 --> 06:23.888
I'm sorry, I'm just a little distracted.

06:23.913 --> 06:25.071
Okay, you know what?

06:25.096 --> 06:26.762
I'm making an executive decision

06:26.787 --> 06:28.540
and we are shutting down
the bar early tonight.

06:28.565 --> 06:29.246
Why?

06:29.271 --> 06:31.255
Oh, because we're having a barbecue.

06:31.382 --> 06:32.847
Yeah, your friends, my friends,

06:32.872 --> 06:35.717
charred meat, stiff drinks, big laughs.

06:36.818 --> 06:38.799
Come on, you need it.

06:40.079 --> 06:41.535
Yeah, I think I do.

06:41.560 --> 06:43.199
All right, it's done.

06:43.224 --> 06:45.288
- We'll figure out the rest later.
- Cool.

06:45.313 --> 06:48.404
I'll get Taylor and Bird
to help with the food.

06:49.507 --> 06:51.041
You're kind of amazing, you know that?

06:51.066 --> 06:52.847
As long as you realize.

