07:02.658 --> 07:04.372
Wow.

07:05.475 --> 07:07.251
This doesn't even look like the same room.

07:07.276 --> 07:08.839
You're a miracle worker.

07:08.864 --> 07:09.858
The bones were there.

07:09.883 --> 07:11.383
I just needed to polish it up.

07:12.286 --> 07:14.910
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

07:17.328 --> 07:20.848
You didn't happen to speak
to Carter today, did you?

07:21.200 --> 07:22.685
No.

07:22.710 --> 07:24.177
I thought she was at work.

07:24.202 --> 07:25.536
Yeah.

07:25.673 --> 07:28.334
I guess that's probably where she is.

07:28.359 --> 07:29.467
Everything okay?

07:29.492 --> 07:31.926
Just some mother-daughter drama.

07:31.951 --> 07:33.049
What about you?

07:33.074 --> 07:34.881
Everything okay?

07:37.908 --> 07:41.509
Actually, I was wondering if, um...

07:43.335 --> 07:45.348
I'm thinking you've probably

07:45.373 --> 07:47.823
been to a couple parole hearings.

07:48.228 --> 07:49.896
Yeah, a few.

07:49.921 --> 07:52.833
My dad is up for parole.

07:53.007 --> 07:55.575
So I'm going to testify.

07:56.135 --> 07:57.635
Make sure that they keep him in.

07:57.660 --> 07:59.353
Did the parole board contact you?

07:59.378 --> 08:00.144
Yeah.

08:00.169 --> 08:01.840
Okay, so you just go.

08:01.865 --> 08:03.224
You tell them your story,

08:03.249 --> 08:05.161
and because it's coming from his son,

08:05.186 --> 08:06.953
it'll have a lot of influence.

08:06.978 --> 08:08.645
Okay.

08:08.916 --> 08:11.617
Do you think that he'll... be there?

08:11.642 --> 08:13.443
He's gonna be there.

08:13.468 --> 08:15.004
I can go with you if you want.

08:15.029 --> 08:16.191
I'd be happy to.

08:16.216 --> 08:18.640
I think it's just something
I need to do on my own.

08:18.665 --> 08:19.514
Of course.

08:19.540 --> 08:21.894
Just let me know if you need anything.

08:21.931 --> 08:23.565
You could, uh...

08:23.590 --> 08:26.383
you could hammer in a
few nails while I'm gone.

08:26.408 --> 08:28.462
Well, not unless you want
the whole house to fall down.

08:28.487 --> 08:31.250
♪

08:43.107 --> 08:44.711
Hi.

08:45.868 --> 08:47.684
Hey.

08:47.709 --> 08:50.357
Uh, Jared, this is Lori.

08:50.382 --> 08:52.201
- Lori, Jared.
- Hey, nice to meet you.

08:52.226 --> 08:53.859
You as well, I've heard good things.

08:53.884 --> 08:55.226
All lies.

08:55.251 --> 08:56.496
(cell phone vibrating)

08:56.521 --> 08:58.429
I'm sorry, one second.

08:58.454 --> 08:59.992
Hey.

09:01.126 --> 09:02.281
Very cute.

09:02.306 --> 09:04.263
Oh, thanks.

09:04.806 --> 09:07.642
Um, so what brings you here?

09:07.667 --> 09:09.287
Ben wanted me to let you know

09:09.312 --> 09:11.232
that he got Olivia checked into rehab

09:11.257 --> 09:12.370
and everything's going well.

09:12.395 --> 09:13.483
That's great.

09:13.508 --> 09:14.450
Thank you for telling me.

09:14.475 --> 09:15.615
Of course.

09:16.128 --> 09:18.459
Yeah, that was the vodka guy.

09:18.484 --> 09:20.192
He got a flat tire, again.

09:20.479 --> 09:21.845
Can I get you a drink?

09:21.878 --> 09:23.299
A cranberry juice would be great.

09:23.324 --> 09:23.993
All right.

09:24.018 --> 09:26.770
Um, I'm gonna need to
see some ID, young lady.

09:26.795 --> 09:28.265
(laughing)

09:28.290 --> 09:30.317
Okay, wow.

09:30.342 --> 09:33.411
I don't remember the last
time somebody carded me.

09:33.436 --> 09:34.370
He's kidding.

09:34.395 --> 09:37.291
Hey, let the old lady have her thrill.

09:39.936 --> 09:42.099
Hey, happy birthday.

09:42.124 --> 09:43.257
Thank you.

09:43.282 --> 09:44.680
Wait, today's the 29th?

09:44.704 --> 09:46.175
All day.

09:46.200 --> 09:47.444
Oh, um...

09:47.469 --> 09:48.760
Happy birthday.

09:48.785 --> 09:50.429
How are you celebrating?

09:50.454 --> 09:52.855
I'm... not really sure.

09:55.083 --> 09:58.090
Uh, well, you know, we're having a barbecue

09:58.115 --> 10:00.107
here later if you wanted to come.

10:00.132 --> 10:01.505
I would love to.

10:01.530 --> 10:03.563
I mean, if you're sure that's okay.

10:03.588 --> 10:04.744
Yeah.

10:04.769 --> 10:05.674
Yeah, it's okay.

10:05.699 --> 10:07.285
Thanks.

10:07.311 --> 10:10.263
Then... I guess I'll see you later tonight.

10:10.288 --> 10:11.180
See you later.

10:11.205 --> 10:13.162
- Have a good one.
- Bye.

10:15.094 --> 10:17.993
♪

10:19.743 --> 10:22.407
That was really nice,
what you just did for her.

10:22.432 --> 10:25.553
Oh, well, I don't want her
to be alone on her birthday.

10:25.624 --> 10:27.376
You're kind of amazing, you know that?

10:27.401 --> 10:28.759
(chuckling)

10:28.784 --> 10:30.690
As long as you realize.

10:34.244 --> 10:36.909
Okay, it's like the
unspoken relationship law.

10:36.909 --> 10:38.520
Inviting the besties and partying

10:38.545 --> 10:39.896
means you're a real thing.

10:39.922 --> 10:41.779
Wait, I thought you
already were a real thing.

10:41.803 --> 10:43.957
Yeah, but after tonight,
there's no going back.

10:43.982 --> 10:45.482
God, it's so weird.

10:45.507 --> 10:47.194
A couple weeks ago, I was in school.

10:47.219 --> 10:48.466
Now I'm out, working,

10:48.491 --> 10:50.633
and in some like new relationship.

10:50.658 --> 10:51.588
With a grown-up.

10:51.613 --> 10:52.524
It was bound to happen.

10:52.549 --> 10:54.508
We need guys who are as mature as we are.

10:54.533 --> 10:56.128
As you seem to already know.

10:56.153 --> 10:57.463
Oh, yeah, that's me.

10:57.488 --> 10:59.070
Always ahead of the curve.

10:59.095 --> 11:00.973
So you couldn't change
Max's mind about tonight?

11:00.998 --> 11:01.979
No.

11:02.004 --> 11:04.135
I think he's just distracting
himself with work.

11:04.160 --> 11:06.364
Distracting himself from what?

11:06.389 --> 11:07.671
Long story.

11:07.696 --> 11:09.753
Are you sure you couldn't use
your powers of persuasion?

11:09.778 --> 11:12.825
Believe me, I would like
nothing better, but no can do.

11:12.850 --> 11:13.532
You know what?

11:13.557 --> 11:14.887
I think we need to do a triple date soon.

11:14.912 --> 11:16.500
Get all our hot guys together.

11:16.525 --> 11:17.754
Ah, yes.

11:17.780 --> 11:20.471
A definite upside to dating older.

11:20.496 --> 11:22.955
- The sexy.
- Yeah?

11:22.980 --> 11:24.858
Um, except...

11:24.883 --> 11:26.417
What?

11:26.441 --> 11:28.448
Well, I just assumed
that dating an older guy

11:28.473 --> 11:29.751
with more experience,

11:29.776 --> 11:32.167
he would take me to a different place,

11:32.192 --> 11:33.760
sexually speaking.

11:33.786 --> 11:35.296
What place is that?

11:35.321 --> 11:37.601
Do you mean like funky positions?

11:37.625 --> 11:40.727
'Cause Max has this weird
book from like the '70s...

11:40.752 --> 11:43.378
No, um... you know,

11:43.403 --> 11:44.998
a place where everyone in a relationship

11:45.024 --> 11:46.863
reaches the same goal.

11:46.888 --> 11:48.902
Orgasmically speaking?

11:48.927 --> 11:51.109
- Exactly.
- You mean you haven't?

11:51.134 --> 11:53.085
Well, so far, the only person who's been

11:53.110 --> 11:55.111
able to take care of business

11:55.136 --> 11:57.606
has been, well... me.

11:57.966 --> 11:59.580
Oh.

11:59.605 --> 12:00.922
Come on, it's not a big deal.

12:00.947 --> 12:02.711
You can't tell me that every
guy you've been with has...

12:02.736 --> 12:04.304
- Yeah.
- Pretty much, yeah.

12:04.329 --> 12:05.843
All right, well, I'm gonna go hunt down

12:05.868 --> 12:06.800
what's left of my dignity.

12:06.825 --> 12:08.244
- Bird, come on.
- No.

12:08.269 --> 12:09.155
It's fine.

12:09.180 --> 12:11.105
Look, we forgot the avocados.

12:11.130 --> 12:13.125
I'm gonna go grab some.

12:17.387 --> 12:19.616
Hey, have you talked to Mom?

12:19.870 --> 12:22.130
I don't know what more there is to say.

12:22.155 --> 12:23.379
She made it pretty clear.

12:23.404 --> 12:25.625
It's her way or the highway.

12:25.651 --> 12:28.852
You're not actually
gonna move out, are you?

12:28.877 --> 12:30.878
Look, I'm just trying to live my life.

12:30.903 --> 12:33.347
She let me drop out of
school, for God's sake,

12:33.372 --> 12:35.414
and now she's all over me
like I'm five years old?

12:35.439 --> 12:37.885
Yeah, I know, she's not
great about boundaries.

12:37.910 --> 12:40.165
But she means well.

12:40.395 --> 12:41.434
Oh.

12:41.459 --> 12:42.664
Speaking of boundaries,

12:42.689 --> 12:44.486
just so it doesn't surprise you tonight,

12:44.511 --> 12:46.093
Lori's gonna be there.

12:46.920 --> 12:48.354
Why?

12:48.389 --> 12:50.151
It's her birthday.

12:50.176 --> 12:51.085
Are you serious?

12:51.110 --> 12:52.610
That's what we're doing?

12:52.635 --> 12:55.111
- Having a birthday party for Lori?
- No.

12:55.136 --> 12:57.510
We are having a barbecue,
it just happens to be

12:57.535 --> 12:58.504
Lori's birthday

12:58.529 --> 13:00.408
and Ben's out of town and she's all alone.

13:00.433 --> 13:01.194
Oh my God.

13:01.219 --> 13:02.954
Bird has never climaxed with a guy

13:02.979 --> 13:05.842
and we're having a birthday
celebration for Lori.

13:05.867 --> 13:08.407
We are officially entering
"The Twilight Zone," Carter.

13:08.432 --> 13:11.064
♪

13:15.585 --> 13:17.289
Oh, hey.

13:18.022 --> 13:20.409
- I thought Taylor might be down here.
- Nope.

13:20.434 --> 13:21.745
Well, I have a chem paper I was hoping

13:21.770 --> 13:22.488
she would proof.

13:22.513 --> 13:23.780
- Do you know when she'll be back?
- Late.

13:23.805 --> 13:25.209
She's with Bird and Carter.

13:25.234 --> 13:27.635
Jared's having something at his bar.

13:27.660 --> 13:29.325
Then what are you doing here?

13:29.536 --> 13:31.157
Working.

13:31.182 --> 13:34.381
And you're cool with her
going to a party solo?

13:34.406 --> 13:35.629
Yes.

13:35.654 --> 13:38.610
I just figured after what
happened on the college trip,

13:38.635 --> 13:41.031
- you know, you'd want to...
- She doesn't need a babysitter.

13:41.201 --> 13:42.665
Did something happen?

13:42.913 --> 13:44.722
Did I miss something,
'cause you seem squeezed.

13:44.747 --> 13:47.344
I just have a lot of work
to do, so if you don't mind?

13:47.369 --> 13:50.190
All right... cool.

13:52.629 --> 13:55.117
Look, man, I get it, all right?

13:55.142 --> 13:56.543
I was there for Taylor when you weren't

13:56.568 --> 13:57.916
and you're bent out of shape about it,

13:57.941 --> 13:59.060
but it's all good.

13:59.084 --> 14:00.916
- She's okay.
- You know what?

14:00.942 --> 14:03.934
I don't need you to tell
me how my girlfriend is.

14:06.997 --> 14:08.671
Whatever, dude.

14:08.696 --> 14:10.581
I knew her way before you came along

14:10.606 --> 14:11.870
and I'll know her long after you're gone.

14:11.895 --> 14:13.462
♪

14:14.566 --> 14:16.752
(grunting)

14:22.430 --> 14:24.640
(Elizabeth) Hey, hey, cut it out!

14:24.665 --> 14:26.456
Stop it right now!

14:38.245 --> 14:39.412
What's going on here?

14:39.437 --> 14:40.351
Well?

14:40.376 --> 14:41.913
Whoa, what the hell?

14:41.937 --> 14:43.187
Did you guys throw down?

14:43.212 --> 14:45.799
- Cool.
- No, no, not cool.

14:45.824 --> 14:48.258
You know, I know you both
have a lot on your mind,

14:48.283 --> 14:50.687
but this is unacceptable.

14:50.712 --> 14:51.981
I know and I'm sorry.

14:52.006 --> 14:53.129
I'm gonna clean all of it up.

14:53.154 --> 14:55.215
You bet your ass you
will... Both of you will.

14:55.239 --> 14:56.110
- Sure.
- I've got it.

14:56.135 --> 14:57.270
I don't need his help.

14:57.295 --> 14:59.375
Damn... I miss all the good stuff.

14:59.400 --> 15:02.577
Okay, you both did this,
you're both cleaning up.

15:02.602 --> 15:04.737
And might I suggest, while you're doing it,

15:04.762 --> 15:07.171
you sort out what got you
worked up in the first place.

15:07.196 --> 15:08.877
- It's all fine.
- Whatever.

15:08.903 --> 15:10.915
All right, I've got to head out, so...

15:10.940 --> 15:13.474
Grant, I'm putting you in charge.

15:13.498 --> 15:14.202
Seriously?

15:14.227 --> 15:16.008
Oh my God, this is awesome.

15:16.033 --> 15:17.033
I'm in charge.

15:17.058 --> 15:19.088
Both of you, work it out.

15:21.206 --> 15:23.307
Chop-chop, put your back into it.

15:23.332 --> 15:25.037
I mean it.

15:26.364 --> 15:29.433
♪ I will follow you ♪

15:29.458 --> 15:33.284
♪ To the end of the world ♪

15:33.309 --> 15:35.474
♪ With you ♪

15:35.499 --> 15:37.055
I thought the only things we
could make in my kitchen...

15:37.080 --> 15:38.055
Yes, I did.

15:38.080 --> 15:40.352
Check out that boyfriend-sister banter.

15:40.384 --> 15:41.929
I think my heart is melting.

15:41.954 --> 15:43.553
You know what, I actually
think this is a good thing.

15:43.578 --> 15:44.878
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

15:44.904 --> 15:46.545
And your mom will chill eventually.

15:46.678 --> 15:48.093
Yeah, I know.

15:48.118 --> 15:49.358
I just wish she wouldn't make everything

15:49.383 --> 15:50.784
so hard in the meantime.

15:50.809 --> 15:52.544
Speaking of which, is Lori
actually coming tonight?

15:52.569 --> 15:53.751
Yeah.

15:54.355 --> 15:56.958
So bizarre, inviting her back into my life.

15:56.983 --> 15:58.201
Never in a million years

15:58.226 --> 15:59.972
thought I'd see this day coming.

16:02.132 --> 16:03.332
♪

16:03.357 --> 16:05.178
Here goes nothing.

16:07.373 --> 16:09.080
- Hey.
- Hey.

16:09.105 --> 16:11.128
- This is so nice.
- Thanks.

16:11.153 --> 16:13.804
- Yeah, it turned out all right.
- Yeah.

16:14.136 --> 16:15.819
You didn't have to invite me.

16:15.843 --> 16:18.441
No, come on, you shouldn't
be alone on your birthday.

16:18.467 --> 16:21.108
Come in, I'll take your jacket.

16:28.976 --> 16:30.906
<i>♪ I will take another step ♪</i>

16:30.931 --> 16:33.754
<i>♪ Yes I will take
another step for you ♪</i>

16:34.459 --> 16:35.651
<i>♪ Oh... ♪</i>

16:35.676 --> 16:37.263
- Oh, hey, guys.
- Hey.

16:37.289 --> 16:39.383
Tay, you remember Seth, right?

16:39.408 --> 16:40.959
Yeah, from the house party.

16:40.984 --> 16:42.556
Top of your class, 4.0.

16:42.581 --> 16:44.447
You don't do taxes by any chance, do you?

16:44.472 --> 16:46.478
You are right, he's funny.

16:46.503 --> 16:47.968
Oh, he's a lot more than that.

16:47.993 --> 16:50.431
Okay, I'm gonna go see
if Carter needs any help.

16:53.793 --> 16:55.369
Does she seem happy?

16:55.394 --> 16:56.551
Definitely.

16:56.576 --> 16:58.232
Yeah, she's crazy about you.

16:58.257 --> 16:59.568
It's mutual.

16:59.593 --> 17:01.599
We have a great time together.

17:01.624 --> 17:03.169
I just feel like maybe I could

17:03.194 --> 17:05.462
be doing more for her, you know?

17:05.487 --> 17:06.854
Well...

17:06.878 --> 17:08.279
Tell me, please.

17:08.304 --> 17:09.895
Look, this is the real deal.

17:09.920 --> 17:11.457
Okay.

17:11.481 --> 17:13.336
You didn't hear this from me,

17:13.362 --> 17:15.873
but if you really want
to make her smile...

17:15.897 --> 17:16.838
Yeah?

17:16.863 --> 17:19.063
Ask her what she likes.

17:19.088 --> 17:21.509
Like... like in graphic detail,

17:21.534 --> 17:22.820
and I mean graphic,

17:22.847 --> 17:25.182
like in every aspect of your relationship.

17:25.207 --> 17:26.718
I'm not sure I follow.

17:27.134 --> 17:30.006
Trust me, just... ask her.

17:30.031 --> 17:31.326
Like...

17:31.351 --> 17:33.127
Yeah, like...

17:34.176 --> 17:36.376
(Grant) I mean, I've heard
of the Cone of Silence,

17:36.401 --> 17:38.435
but this is more like
the basement of gloom.

17:38.460 --> 17:40.045
Come on, at least give me a play-by-play

17:40.070 --> 17:41.741
of whose cranium blew threw the drywall.

17:41.766 --> 17:43.937
Grant, right now is not the time, man.

17:43.962 --> 17:45.097
Don't shoot the messenger.

17:45.122 --> 17:46.347
He's just trying to lighten the mood.

17:46.372 --> 17:47.508
How about we just work?

17:47.533 --> 17:48.854
The sooner we're done, the sooner

17:48.879 --> 17:50.247
you can get out of here.

17:50.272 --> 17:52.452
You know, I'm really starting to think your

17:52.477 --> 17:55.414
whole Zen master deal is just a façade,

17:55.439 --> 17:57.545
'cause the cracks are
really starting to show.

17:57.570 --> 17:59.819
Um, when I was encouraging us all to talk,

17:59.844 --> 18:01.178
I was imagining it, you know,

18:01.203 --> 18:03.588
a little less hostile, more chummy.

18:03.613 --> 18:04.644
I don't see that happening.

18:04.669 --> 18:06.070
Yeah, not really in a jokey mood.

18:06.095 --> 18:07.680
There you go, see?

18:07.705 --> 18:09.936
Something you both agree
on, that's good, right?

18:09.961 --> 18:13.369
Finding common ground is the
first step to mending fences.

18:14.039 --> 18:15.521
Read that on a greeting card.

18:15.546 --> 18:17.353
You know, I appreciate you

18:17.379 --> 18:19.876
trying to referee and all, but you realize

18:19.901 --> 18:21.902
that you don't have to be
here if you don't want.

18:21.927 --> 18:23.561
- We won't tell your mom.
- Yeah.

18:23.586 --> 18:25.450
You can take off anytime.

18:25.475 --> 18:26.209
Nope.

18:26.234 --> 18:27.699
I'm good here.

18:27.724 --> 18:29.827
There's no way I'm missing round two.

18:30.929 --> 18:33.997
♪

18:55.563 --> 18:57.994
(keys clacking)

19:16.717 --> 19:19.565
So do you actually know
any of these people?

19:19.590 --> 19:22.734
Uh... that's the guy who sold me my couch.

19:22.759 --> 19:24.656
Ah, from Craigslist.

19:24.681 --> 19:26.337
Craigslist Carl, that's what we call him.

19:26.362 --> 19:27.744
Nice, he has that vibe.

19:27.769 --> 19:29.904
- _
- (cell phone vibrating)

19:32.695 --> 19:34.472
It's just my other boyfriend.

19:34.497 --> 19:36.008
Just won't leave me alone.

19:36.033 --> 19:40.031
Y'all do know how to throw
a party, big or small.

19:40.236 --> 19:41.904
Hey, Stevie.

19:41.929 --> 19:43.808
Did you get that thing
I asked you to bring?

19:43.833 --> 19:44.766
In the kitchen.

19:44.791 --> 19:46.304
What thing?

19:46.726 --> 19:48.489
You'll find out soon enough.

19:48.514 --> 19:50.696
Okay.

19:51.639 --> 19:53.541
The guacamole is excellent.

19:53.566 --> 19:55.227
I already had thirds.

19:55.252 --> 19:57.943
Um... any chance I could get a recipe?

19:57.968 --> 19:59.088
The recipe?

19:59.113 --> 20:00.343
Really?

20:00.661 --> 20:01.986
Look, I get it.

20:02.010 --> 20:03.400
Um, I just thought...

20:03.425 --> 20:05.203
What?

20:05.228 --> 20:08.252
Well, Carter seems okay with my being here.

20:08.276 --> 20:10.039
Yeah, she is trying really hard to see

20:10.064 --> 20:11.603
the new-and-improved you,

20:11.628 --> 20:13.219
but every time I look at you,

20:13.244 --> 20:16.611
all I see is a giant toxic cloud,

20:16.636 --> 20:20.259
so I'm sorry if I don't
feel like swapping recipes

20:20.284 --> 20:22.147
with you just yet.

20:22.172 --> 20:24.459
Yeah, I doubt that I ever will.

20:27.250 --> 20:28.812
What are you up to?

20:28.837 --> 20:30.512
Jared said we could use his office.

20:30.537 --> 20:32.465
For what?

20:35.484 --> 20:38.113
Oh, that's what you're up to.

20:39.407 --> 20:40.865
You okay with this?

20:40.890 --> 20:42.923
Actually, I think it's
kinda hot that everybody's

20:42.948 --> 20:44.790
- just outside the door.
- I know.

20:44.815 --> 20:46.517
There's something about
almost getting caught.

20:46.542 --> 20:48.947
Says the guy who just locked the door.

20:48.972 --> 20:51.331
The "almost" is key.

20:52.158 --> 20:53.909
Is there anything else you like?

20:53.934 --> 20:55.828
You mean besides you?

20:58.175 --> 20:59.419
Look...

20:59.444 --> 21:01.473
I want to make you feel good,

21:01.498 --> 21:04.338
in like an epic way.

21:06.505 --> 21:08.370
So tell me what to do.

21:08.442 --> 21:11.408
How about I just show you instead?

21:13.452 --> 21:17.821
♪ Oh ♪

21:19.788 --> 21:20.875
Looks like we did good, babe.

21:20.900 --> 21:21.628
What do you think?

21:21.653 --> 21:23.909
Yeah, I think we did very good.

21:23.934 --> 21:25.404
You should make a toast.

21:25.430 --> 21:26.967
You first.

21:26.992 --> 21:29.606
- Okay.
- Really? Okay.

21:30.975 --> 21:32.522
I'd like to make a toast.

21:32.547 --> 21:35.021
To old friends and new friends,

21:35.046 --> 21:38.299
which are sometimes the best
family a guy could ask for.

21:39.750 --> 21:41.093
Cheers.

21:41.118 --> 21:43.242
(all) Cheers.

21:43.267 --> 21:45.002
Ah, you're up.

21:45.027 --> 21:46.443
Okay.

21:49.117 --> 21:52.018
Wow, I don't really know where to start.

21:52.043 --> 21:54.843
Um... okay.

21:54.868 --> 22:00.063
So I don't know much about this
life, but I do know this...

22:00.734 --> 22:02.473
you are only as good

22:02.498 --> 22:05.099
as the people you surround yourself with

22:05.124 --> 22:09.479
and I'm so lucky to be
surrounded by all of you.

22:11.210 --> 22:12.656
Cheers.

22:12.681 --> 22:14.394
(all) Cheers.

22:14.419 --> 22:17.319
And to add to that, one more little thing.

22:19.651 --> 22:21.070
Happy birthday.

22:21.095 --> 22:22.838
My gosh, you guys.

22:22.863 --> 22:24.545
Thank you.

22:24.570 --> 22:26.136
Happy birthday.

22:26.161 --> 22:28.106
Wow.

22:38.537 --> 22:40.148
What are you doing here?

22:40.173 --> 22:41.908
<i>Please tell me I didn't just interrupt you</i>

22:41.933 --> 22:43.654
celebrating Lori's birthday.

22:43.679 --> 22:45.429
No, that's not what this is.

22:45.454 --> 22:46.960
Not that it's any of your business.

22:46.985 --> 22:49.247
I don't live under your
roof anymore, remember?

22:49.272 --> 22:50.419
So it's official.

22:50.444 --> 22:51.444
You're moving out.

22:51.469 --> 22:52.770
That seems to be what you want.

22:52.795 --> 22:55.043
Carter, I never said that.

22:55.068 --> 22:56.321
Look, you don't know what

22:56.346 --> 22:57.510
you're getting yourself into here.

22:57.535 --> 22:59.369
I'm not getting myself into anything.

22:59.394 --> 23:01.767
We didn't even know it was
her birthday until today.

23:01.792 --> 23:04.074
We had already planned this
and we only invited her

23:04.099 --> 23:05.401
because we didn't want her to be alone.

23:05.426 --> 23:06.927
I'm not talking about Lori.

23:06.952 --> 23:08.643
I'm talking about Jared.

23:08.668 --> 23:10.388
What about Jared?

23:10.840 --> 23:13.124
Did you know he's married...

23:13.149 --> 23:14.850
and has a daughter?

23:14.875 --> 23:16.275
What?

23:16.300 --> 23:17.592
I guess you didn't.

23:17.617 --> 23:20.521
Mom, I work with him every night.

23:20.546 --> 23:22.627
I've... I've been to his apartment.

23:22.652 --> 23:24.075
I would know if he was married.

23:24.101 --> 23:25.829
I did a background check on him, Carter.

23:25.853 --> 23:27.051
I'm telling you the truth.

23:27.076 --> 23:28.576
- Mom?
- Hey.

23:28.601 --> 23:29.971
What's going on?

23:29.997 --> 23:32.036
(Jared) Everything all right?

23:32.061 --> 23:34.059
Do you want to ask him or should I?

23:34.084 --> 23:35.471
Ask me what?

23:35.825 --> 23:38.323
Tell them it's not true, Jared.

23:39.407 --> 23:42.868
Tell them you're not married with a kid.

23:50.226 --> 23:52.901
It's not how I wanted you to find out.

23:53.473 --> 23:55.574
What?

23:55.603 --> 23:58.016
I wanted to tell you.

23:58.041 --> 24:00.231
I was gonna tell you, I just...

24:00.256 --> 24:02.909
I was waiting for the time to be right.

24:02.934 --> 24:04.373
(scoffing)

24:04.399 --> 24:06.855
When was the time ever going to be right

24:06.880 --> 24:09.314
for you to tell me
something like that, Jared?

24:09.339 --> 24:10.372
Carter.

24:10.397 --> 24:11.878
Carter!

24:11.903 --> 24:13.966
You know, it's not what it looks like.

24:13.990 --> 24:16.198
Don't try to spin this with me.

24:16.224 --> 24:17.590
I'm a cop.

24:17.615 --> 24:20.639
I deal with bigger, badder
asshats than you every day.

24:20.664 --> 24:21.714
Mom, let's get out of here.

24:21.739 --> 24:23.689
So you're married, you have a kid,

24:23.714 --> 24:25.815
you hire underage girls and
then you sleep with them.

24:25.840 --> 24:27.059
What else don't we know about you?

24:27.084 --> 24:28.875
Is this place even permitted?

24:28.900 --> 24:30.733
Do you even have a liquor license?

24:30.758 --> 24:33.593
Are you here on official business, Officer?

24:33.618 --> 24:35.552
Or is this a personal matter?

24:35.577 --> 24:36.921
Looks like both to me.

24:36.945 --> 24:39.943
Okay, okay, we're leaving now.

24:45.494 --> 24:47.094
(door closing)

24:47.119 --> 24:49.482
Look, I know you mean well, but...

24:49.507 --> 24:51.644
you can't put Carter on the spot like that.

24:51.669 --> 24:53.112
She's in way over her head.

24:53.138 --> 24:55.279
Okay, I get that, but you...

24:55.304 --> 24:57.072
You kind of came off like a crazy person.

24:57.097 --> 24:58.565
I'm crazy, really?

24:58.590 --> 25:00.654
You guys were just in there
celebrating the birthday

25:00.679 --> 25:02.382
of the woman who kidnapped your sister

25:02.407 --> 25:03.752
and held a gun to my head.

25:03.777 --> 25:05.372
You know it's more complicated than that.

25:05.397 --> 25:06.829
Actually, it's not, Taylor.

25:06.854 --> 25:09.058
Mom, this party was for Carter,

25:09.083 --> 25:10.617
who's been pretty bummed
since you practically

25:10.642 --> 25:11.821
kicked her out this morning.

25:11.846 --> 25:14.242
I didn't kick her out.

25:15.512 --> 25:17.637
I would never kick her out.

25:17.662 --> 25:21.112
You know, I try really
hard to be the cool mom,

25:21.137 --> 25:24.037
or the understanding mom,

25:24.062 --> 25:26.797
or, you know, the best
mom that I know how to be.

25:26.822 --> 25:28.520
And clearly that's not working.

25:28.545 --> 25:30.177
You guys are just butting heads right now,

25:30.202 --> 25:32.929
but she knows underneath it
all that you're a great mom.

25:32.954 --> 25:34.455
You could have fooled me.

25:34.480 --> 25:37.417
Mom, you have had so much on your plate

25:37.442 --> 25:40.932
since Dad's been away,
and you are doing so well.

25:40.957 --> 25:42.958
I'm serious.

25:42.983 --> 25:46.983
But you gotta try to stop
controlling everything.

25:47.008 --> 25:49.359
I'm just trying to be a good mom.

25:49.384 --> 25:52.744
By humiliating her in front of everyone?

25:52.990 --> 25:55.273
You know that's only gonna
drive her further away.

25:55.298 --> 25:56.578
It's just...

25:56.602 --> 25:59.696
in my head, I thought I was
coming here to fix things.

25:59.721 --> 26:00.952
I need to protect her.

26:00.977 --> 26:03.465
I thought I was showing her that I cared.

26:03.490 --> 26:05.007
I know.

26:05.032 --> 26:08.353
And you did, so maybe we just...

26:08.640 --> 26:10.817
give it a rest tonight.

26:10.842 --> 26:13.067
Okay, give her a chance
to make the next move,

26:13.092 --> 26:16.157
whatever that may be.

26:16.182 --> 26:18.279
(sighing)

26:18.304 --> 26:20.748
Take a break.

26:23.884 --> 26:27.545
Clearly, I haven't done everything wrong.

26:27.570 --> 26:30.151
I have my moments.

26:32.899 --> 26:34.929
Hey.

26:35.068 --> 26:37.833
Thank you for everything.

26:37.858 --> 26:39.580
This was a really wonderful night.

26:39.605 --> 26:41.040
Yeah, thanks for coming.

26:41.065 --> 26:43.022
I don't know what went on
with Elizabeth in there,

26:43.047 --> 26:45.482
but... be good to Carter, okay?

26:45.507 --> 26:47.461
She's been through a lot.

26:47.487 --> 26:48.720
She deserves a break.

26:48.745 --> 26:50.446
Yeah, that's...

26:50.471 --> 26:52.893
that's all I'm trying to give her.

26:53.452 --> 26:55.478
Thanks.

26:58.370 --> 26:59.831
(sighing)

26:59.856 --> 27:02.568
♪

27:02.593 --> 27:04.078
(Seth) You sure you're good.

27:04.103 --> 27:05.956
(Bird) Yeah.

27:05.981 --> 27:06.861
You're not?

27:06.886 --> 27:08.710
Yeah, I'm great.

27:08.735 --> 27:11.823
I just want to make sure
I'm not missing anything.

27:11.847 --> 27:13.661
Wait, what are you getting at?

27:13.687 --> 27:15.086
Nothing.

27:15.111 --> 27:17.597
Wait, did somebody say something to you?

27:17.622 --> 27:18.966
It might have been mentioned.

27:18.991 --> 27:21.110
So that's why you have all these questions.

27:21.135 --> 27:22.591
Yeah.

27:23.335 --> 27:26.246
So... have I done it yet?

27:27.067 --> 27:29.005
I'm sorry.

27:29.030 --> 27:30.203
You know what, maybe it's just me or...

27:30.228 --> 27:31.662
No, no, no, you're perfect.

27:31.687 --> 27:33.167
It's clearly an operating error,

27:33.192 --> 27:34.978
but we'll get there.

27:35.003 --> 27:39.070
♪ I need that animal high ♪

27:41.279 --> 27:43.311
(door opening)

27:47.128 --> 27:50.150
You don't know how happy I am to see you.

27:50.927 --> 27:52.961
I just...

27:53.156 --> 27:55.070
have to understand this.

27:55.095 --> 27:56.029
Good.

27:56.054 --> 27:57.136
'Cause I want to explain.

27:57.161 --> 27:59.857
When I told you I lied about my age...

27:59.882 --> 28:01.247
you were livid.

28:01.273 --> 28:02.890
I know.

28:05.069 --> 28:08.706
I felt like we'd already had so much drama,

28:08.731 --> 28:10.809
and I didn't know where this was going,

28:10.834 --> 28:13.105
and then I got scared that...

28:13.630 --> 28:15.485
it might freak you out.

28:15.510 --> 28:17.705
So it's true.

28:18.294 --> 28:19.935
You have a wife.

28:19.960 --> 28:21.762
And a daughter.

28:22.358 --> 28:23.673
Oh my God.

28:23.698 --> 28:25.227
Carter, it's...

28:26.078 --> 28:28.616
it's been over a long time.

28:28.641 --> 28:30.082
We're separated.

28:30.107 --> 28:31.465
Okay.

28:31.490 --> 28:33.337
Uh...

28:33.362 --> 28:35.602
how long were you together?

28:35.627 --> 28:36.954
Less than a year.

28:36.979 --> 28:38.569
Did you love her?

28:39.444 --> 28:41.456
In the beginning, yeah.

28:41.481 --> 28:43.121
We started fighting all the time

28:43.146 --> 28:45.112
and things went south pretty fast.

28:45.137 --> 28:46.674
We broke up and then a week later,

28:46.699 --> 28:49.083
she found out she was pregnant.

28:49.108 --> 28:50.587
So you married her.

28:50.612 --> 28:53.043
I was trying to do the right thing,

28:53.068 --> 28:55.844
for her and our daughter.

28:57.172 --> 29:00.035
But that didn't last long.

29:02.200 --> 29:04.771
You gotta know...

29:05.621 --> 29:07.812
that's all in the past.

29:07.837 --> 29:10.108
All I want now is you.

29:11.181 --> 29:14.228
So why are you still married, Jared?

29:14.253 --> 29:15.938
Why did you not get a divorce?

29:15.963 --> 29:17.963
We've had disagreements about custody,

29:17.989 --> 29:23.404
and she refuses to sign the divorce papers.

29:27.360 --> 29:29.434
(sighing)

29:30.098 --> 29:31.232
You could have told me.

29:31.257 --> 29:32.124
I know.

29:32.149 --> 29:33.997
And I am so sorry.

29:34.021 --> 29:36.770
But, Carter, I see

29:36.795 --> 29:38.929
a future with you...

29:38.954 --> 29:41.419
and my little girl.

29:41.444 --> 29:44.234
I'm falling in love with you.

29:44.592 --> 29:45.925
(sniffling)

29:45.950 --> 29:51.724
(Upbeat jazz music)

29:52.879 --> 29:54.252
Hey.

29:54.277 --> 29:55.994
- Hey.
- You're up early.

29:56.019 --> 29:57.986
Yeah, I couldn't sleep.

29:58.029 --> 29:59.098
Why?

29:59.123 --> 30:01.264
You're not the one who embarrassed herself

30:01.289 --> 30:04.291
in front of a group of
strangers last night.

30:04.316 --> 30:06.202
They weren't all strangers.

30:07.461 --> 30:09.996
Really, why can't you sleep?

30:10.445 --> 30:13.447
I can't stop thinking about Max.

30:13.472 --> 30:14.972
I love him so much.

30:14.997 --> 30:17.012
I just want to be there for him,

30:17.037 --> 30:18.604
you know, like he always is for me.

30:18.629 --> 30:19.503
Yeah.

30:19.528 --> 30:20.795
I know you want to support him,

30:20.820 --> 30:22.518
but you gotta respect his wishes,

30:22.543 --> 30:25.899
even if all your instincts
are screaming otherwise,

30:25.924 --> 30:28.058
or so I'm told.

30:28.083 --> 30:30.233
I just want him to be okay.

30:30.258 --> 30:32.524
Yeah, he exorcised some of his demons

30:32.549 --> 30:33.910
all over our basement.

30:33.935 --> 30:35.918
Oh yeah, I heard about that.

30:36.123 --> 30:38.357
Some people have to let off steam.

30:38.524 --> 30:40.502
Some people do it by running

30:40.527 --> 30:42.031
or hitting golf balls

30:42.056 --> 30:44.505
or humiliating their children.

30:44.530 --> 30:46.525
- Mom.
- I'm joking.

30:46.550 --> 30:47.884
Sort of.

30:48.062 --> 30:49.229
I woke up this morning

30:49.254 --> 30:52.855
just hoping that it was all a bad dream.

30:52.880 --> 30:54.753
Yeah, it happened.

30:54.778 --> 30:56.306
You know where she is?

30:56.331 --> 30:58.800
She was up and out at the crack of dawn.

30:58.825 --> 31:00.926
Avoiding me, obviously.

31:00.951 --> 31:05.973
♪ So you told me you
couldn't take it anymore ♪

31:06.672 --> 31:08.398
♪ Well I know ♪

31:08.423 --> 31:12.469
♪ 'Cause I've been there before ♪

31:15.017 --> 31:16.685
- Carter, hey.
- Hey.

31:16.710 --> 31:18.918
Oh, yeah, you left it at the bar.

31:18.943 --> 31:20.344
Thank you.

31:21.618 --> 31:23.023
You okay?

31:23.048 --> 31:25.065
I guess.

31:25.270 --> 31:27.101
Okay, no, not really.

31:27.126 --> 31:29.092
What happened last night?

31:29.117 --> 31:32.305
Just... I found out some stuff about Jared.

31:32.330 --> 31:34.993
I don't know, he has this whole other life

31:35.018 --> 31:37.720
that happened before me
that he never told me about.

31:37.985 --> 31:39.521
So do you.

31:39.546 --> 31:42.034
With age comes baggage, right?

31:42.059 --> 31:43.393
Yeah, but this is different.

31:43.418 --> 31:45.272
I am trying so hard to be
understanding about this,

31:45.297 --> 31:47.777
but I really don't think
I can move past it.

31:48.588 --> 31:50.723
Take a beat and think it over.

31:50.886 --> 31:52.360
Only you can decide if it's something

31:52.385 --> 31:53.701
you want to sign on for.

31:53.726 --> 31:55.326
Okay.

31:55.351 --> 31:56.495
Thanks.

31:56.520 --> 31:59.260
Yeah, anytime.

31:59.827 --> 32:01.547
Hey, um...

32:01.572 --> 32:03.948
I'm sorry about all of
that drama last night.

32:03.973 --> 32:06.339
I had no idea my mom was
gonna show up like that.

32:06.364 --> 32:08.465
Well, I feel for her.

32:08.490 --> 32:10.512
Watching you leave the nest...

32:11.163 --> 32:12.498
She loves you.

32:12.523 --> 32:13.990
That's all this is.

32:14.015 --> 32:15.415
Well, I wish she had a different way

32:15.440 --> 32:17.463
of showing it sometimes.

32:17.856 --> 32:20.072
I think you should talk to her.

32:20.097 --> 32:21.757
I'm not saying you need to agree with her,

32:21.782 --> 32:23.788
but you should at least try.

32:23.813 --> 32:25.825
You, of all people, are encouraging me

32:25.850 --> 32:27.398
to make up with her.

32:27.424 --> 32:28.501
I know.

32:28.526 --> 32:30.579
But I only want what's best for you.

32:30.859 --> 32:33.205
That's all I've ever wanted.

32:35.606 --> 32:37.982
Come on.

32:39.249 --> 32:41.126
Oh, wow.

32:41.670 --> 32:44.717
I thought we would have
had more work to do today.

32:45.609 --> 32:47.288
Thanks.

32:47.313 --> 32:49.122
- He had someplace to be.
- Oh, yeah?

32:49.147 --> 32:51.648
Yeah, there is a...

32:51.716 --> 32:53.861
parole hearing for his father today.

32:53.886 --> 32:54.952
Really?

32:54.977 --> 32:56.292
They're not gonna let him out, are they?

32:56.317 --> 32:57.250
After what he did?

32:57.275 --> 32:58.186
Well, let's hope not,

32:58.211 --> 32:59.805
but I think he's pretty nervous about it.

32:59.830 --> 33:04.038
Maybe that's why he was on edge yesterday.

33:05.559 --> 33:07.191
Yeah.

33:07.216 --> 33:08.488
Did Taylor go with him?

33:08.513 --> 33:10.176
No, he didn't want any company.

33:10.201 --> 33:14.107
I think he's just struggling
with not having been able to

33:14.132 --> 33:15.637
protect his mom all those years ago.

33:15.662 --> 33:17.030
You know how protective he is.

33:17.055 --> 33:18.455
Yeah, I get that.

33:20.842 --> 33:23.567
I'm sorry about what happened.

33:23.592 --> 33:25.914
I didn't realize that he was stressing.

33:26.121 --> 33:27.938
I should have kept a cooler head.

33:27.963 --> 33:29.066
Gabe.

33:29.091 --> 33:31.407
You're both great kids

33:31.432 --> 33:34.938
and you've been going through a lot lately.

33:35.466 --> 33:36.922
Way too much.

33:36.947 --> 33:38.214
You still think that.

33:38.239 --> 33:40.018
- Really?
- Yeah.

33:40.050 --> 33:42.821
We all get off track once in a while

33:42.846 --> 33:45.261
when we've had a lot to deal with.

33:46.192 --> 33:48.365
It was pretty awful, too.

33:48.961 --> 33:51.509
You just lost your dad.

33:52.230 --> 33:55.021
I knew how much you were hurting.

33:56.471 --> 33:58.796
I need you to know this.

33:59.599 --> 34:02.341
I really loved your father...

34:02.366 --> 34:06.204
which is why I feel the way I do about you.

34:09.079 --> 34:11.217
Thank you.

34:12.853 --> 34:14.793
For hanging in there.

34:14.819 --> 34:17.635
You're very welcome.

34:25.771 --> 34:27.706
What are you doing here?

34:27.732 --> 34:30.045
I heard you had something to take care of.

34:33.913 --> 34:35.920
♪

34:38.376 --> 34:39.681
You ready?

34:39.706 --> 34:41.494
To testify against my dad?

34:41.518 --> 34:43.516
Not quite.

34:43.596 --> 34:44.984
I hear that.

34:45.009 --> 34:47.614
I'm here, if you need me.

34:47.639 --> 34:49.438
That's very stand-up of you.

34:49.464 --> 34:52.772
It's probably hard to believe as of late,

34:52.797 --> 34:55.657
but I can be a stand-up guy.

34:55.681 --> 34:57.844
I know you can.

34:59.077 --> 35:02.344
I appreciate what you did for Taylor.

35:04.366 --> 35:06.487
I shouldn't have thrown it in your face.

35:06.512 --> 35:07.853
That wasn't cool.

35:07.878 --> 35:10.129
I shouldn't have let it get to me.

35:12.935 --> 35:14.760
I'd do most anything

35:14.785 --> 35:16.631
for the people that I care about.

35:17.658 --> 35:19.365
But two different times

35:19.390 --> 35:23.232
now with two people I love most...

35:25.142 --> 35:26.635
bad stuff has gone down

35:26.660 --> 35:28.328
and I wasn't there to help.

35:29.701 --> 35:31.969
You're here now, aren't you?

35:31.994 --> 35:33.807
Might not make a difference.

35:33.832 --> 35:36.129
But you're still fighting.

35:36.154 --> 35:39.551
And you've got me here as backup.

35:40.461 --> 35:42.743
Didn't see that one coming.

35:44.220 --> 35:46.219
Look...

35:46.244 --> 35:48.935
I'll always have feelings for Taylor,

35:48.960 --> 35:52.359
but I respect what it
is the two of you have,

35:52.384 --> 35:55.557
and I will just have to deal with that.

35:57.781 --> 36:00.250
Thanks for coming all the way down here.

36:01.902 --> 36:04.160
No problem.

36:10.707 --> 36:12.040
Still no?

36:12.065 --> 36:14.359
Actually...

36:15.182 --> 36:16.728
yeah.

36:16.753 --> 36:18.040
When?

36:18.066 --> 36:20.238
- Last night.
- Last night?

36:20.262 --> 36:21.948
So what have the last
eight hours been about?

36:21.973 --> 36:22.861
Truth?

36:22.886 --> 36:24.616
Yes, truth.

36:24.641 --> 36:26.451
I got greedy.

36:29.149 --> 36:31.303
Dude, you wanna see that new
horror movie this weekend?

36:31.328 --> 36:33.226
Oh, the one with the dead fish people?

36:33.251 --> 36:35.399
- Yeah, it looks ridiculous.
- I've actually heard it's getting

36:35.424 --> 36:36.726
- pretty killer reviews.
- Really?

36:36.751 --> 36:37.431
Yeah.

36:37.456 --> 36:40.359
Uh, I was told that this was
the scene of an apocalypse.

36:40.384 --> 36:42.030
- No?
- No.

36:42.473 --> 36:43.874
What did I miss?

36:43.899 --> 36:46.039
Why don't I get some sodas for us?

36:46.064 --> 36:48.149
I'll be right back, guys.

36:52.170 --> 36:53.712
Okay.

36:53.737 --> 36:55.239
What is going on?

36:55.263 --> 36:57.862
Gabe showed up for the parole hearing.

36:57.887 --> 36:59.501
I thought you didn't want anyone there.

36:59.526 --> 37:00.425
No, I didn't.

37:00.450 --> 37:03.184
And I thank you for respecting that.

37:03.209 --> 37:04.138
Of course.

37:04.164 --> 37:06.916
Ended up meaning a lot
that he showed up, though.

37:08.739 --> 37:10.241
It was kind of out of control,

37:10.266 --> 37:11.479
but he's a good dude.

37:11.505 --> 37:14.991
And...  maybe I should

37:15.016 --> 37:16.885
ask for help when I need it.

37:17.120 --> 37:20.233
Yeah... maybe.

37:22.327 --> 37:24.308
I love you.

37:24.333 --> 37:25.670
I love you, too.

37:25.695 --> 37:27.014
So how'd it go?

37:27.039 --> 37:28.366
We'll see.

37:28.391 --> 37:30.453
It was weird seeing him.

37:31.206 --> 37:33.335
But I told them why they
shouldn't let him out

37:33.360 --> 37:34.861
and I feel good about that.

37:34.886 --> 37:37.073
Well, I'm glad that Gabe was there for you.

37:37.098 --> 37:38.885
Yeah, me too.

37:39.249 --> 37:41.884
Sounds like I'm the one
who should be jealous.

37:41.983 --> 37:43.926
He and I are going steady.

37:43.951 --> 37:45.023
Shut up.

37:45.047 --> 37:46.901
Gladly.

37:53.870 --> 37:55.071
(sniffling)

37:55.096 --> 37:57.791
- Hey.
- Hey.

37:57.816 --> 37:59.287
You taking over around here?

37:59.312 --> 38:02.434
Just...  missing your dad.

38:02.852 --> 38:05.608
You know how he hums when he writes?

38:05.633 --> 38:06.524
Yes.

38:06.550 --> 38:08.061
Used to drive me crazy.

38:08.086 --> 38:11.037
But now I would kill to hear it.

38:11.061 --> 38:12.772
Life's changed not having him around.

38:12.797 --> 38:15.197
Got used to him being my sounding board.

38:15.222 --> 38:16.719
Even if we disagreed,

38:16.744 --> 38:19.220
he'd always show me the other side,

38:19.298 --> 38:23.332
which is not my strong point, I'm thinking.

38:24.091 --> 38:25.558
Carter...

38:25.585 --> 38:28.173
I am so sorry.

38:29.042 --> 38:30.845
Me too.

38:31.038 --> 38:34.518
Look, I know you were
coming from a good place

38:34.543 --> 38:37.237
and you were just trying
to protect me, but...

38:38.309 --> 38:40.438
you can't ambush me like that.

38:40.463 --> 38:42.044
- I know.
- It's not fair.

38:42.069 --> 38:44.061
And if I could take it back, I would.

38:44.086 --> 38:46.937
I know it's not an excuse, but...

38:46.962 --> 38:49.497
it's very...

38:49.522 --> 38:52.705
difficult for me to watch
you become a woman...

38:53.673 --> 38:55.808
because I really didn't get to see you

38:55.833 --> 38:58.080
being a little girl.

38:59.699 --> 39:01.567
♪

39:01.592 --> 39:03.040
(sniffling)

39:03.065 --> 39:07.121
Well, just FYI, it's just as hard for me.

39:07.761 --> 39:10.376
Sometimes all I want is
to be a little girl again.

39:10.401 --> 39:12.203
Are you getting close with Lori again?

39:12.228 --> 39:14.063
No, I wouldn't exactly say that.

39:14.088 --> 39:16.756
But you're connecting.

39:18.194 --> 39:20.526
Yeah, I guess we are.

39:22.832 --> 39:24.696
I'm trying really hard to handle that,

39:24.721 --> 39:27.664
but it's challenging.

39:28.141 --> 39:32.767
I need you to know that this is your home.

39:34.811 --> 39:38.096
And it will always be your home.

39:42.547 --> 39:44.737
I know.

39:45.769 --> 39:47.937
I just, um...

39:47.962 --> 39:50.312
I just need some space.

39:54.871 --> 39:56.435
(sniffling)

39:56.460 --> 39:58.115
Whoa, whoa.

39:58.140 --> 40:00.136
Don't feel like you have to stay with him

40:00.161 --> 40:01.897
to prove a point to me.

40:01.921 --> 40:03.914
I don't.

40:06.188 --> 40:08.491
Not everything I do is about you.

40:08.516 --> 40:11.200
♪ It's a dream that I forgot ♪

40:11.225 --> 40:14.376
♪ That had not forgotten me ♪

40:14.401 --> 40:17.721
♪ It's returning to my thoughts ♪

40:17.746 --> 40:21.417
♪ And been playing on repeat ♪

40:21.442 --> 40:24.440
♪ It's a film over my eyes ♪

40:24.465 --> 40:28.535
♪ But you're more and more afraid... ♪

40:28.560 --> 40:29.952
Hey.

40:29.977 --> 40:31.368
Um...

40:31.392 --> 40:35.250
So I know Ben's not gonna
be back for a couple of days

40:35.275 --> 40:38.264
and I kind of need a place to stay.

40:38.931 --> 40:40.494
I was wondering if you wouldn't mind

40:40.519 --> 40:42.391
me staying here with you?

40:42.416 --> 40:44.568
Well, of course, you're
always welcome here.

40:44.593 --> 40:46.159
Thank you.

40:46.184 --> 40:48.311
You okay?

40:49.182 --> 40:51.696
I will be.

40:55.777 --> 40:59.977
